---
import Layout from '../../Base.astro';
import SimpleHero from '../../components/SimpleHero.astro';
import FeaturedArticles from '../../components/FeaturedArticles.astro';
import ServicesRelatedWork from '../../components/ServicesRelatedWork.astro';
import '../../styles/pages/_services-list.scss';
---

<Layout
  title="Campaign Management | Florida Marketing Agency"
  description="Campaigns break down when good ideas never turn into coordinated execution. We plan and manage campaigns so the message, timeline, assets, and budget all move in the same direction."
>
  <SimpleHero
    tagline="Digital Marketing Services"
    title="Campaign Management"
    description="Campaigns break down when good ideas never turn into coordinated execution. We plan and manage campaigns so the message, timeline, assets, and budget all move in the same direction."
    lottieFile="campaign-management.json"
  />
  <div class="service-body">
    <div class="wrapper wrapper--narrow">
      <h2>Where teams get stuck</h2>
      <p>
        Campaign problems usually are not about a lack of ideas. They come from too many moving parts with no one
        keeping the strategy, timeline, creative, and budget aligned.
      </p>
      <p>That is when launch dates slip, content arrives late, spend gets wasted, and the campaign never builds the momentum it should.</p>
      <h2>How we fix it</h2>
      <p>
        We help define the campaign story, the rollout plan, the channel mix, and the production rhythm needed to
        support it. Then we manage the details so the work keeps moving after kickoff instead of stalling under its own
        weight.
      </p>
      <h2>What moving forward looks like</h2>
      <p>If you have a launch coming up or an always-on campaign that feels fragmented, we can help shape the plan, organize the deliverables, and keep the execution connected from start to finish.</p>
      <p><a href="/contact/" class="button button--green">Talk Through Your Campaign</a></p>
    </div>
    <ServicesRelatedWork tag={78} />
  </div>
  <FeaturedArticles />
</Layout>
